    "summary": "I am passionate about the work that focuses on inclusive growth in developing countries of South Asia, South-East Asia, and Africa. I have experience in data analysis and modelling by application of mathematical tools and frameworks. I have worked with various small and medium enterprises on business modeling, strategy design, project feasibility analysis, and financial valuations. Also, carried out landscaping studies and analyzed growth potential and investment opportunities in agriculture, clean energy, financial inclusion, and education sectors in India. \n\nI have managed on-ground technical assistance engagements solving critical business issues of enterprises and designed funds such as Energy Impact Fund and a Blended Debt Fund that aims to enable low-cost patient capital to social enterprises.\n\nI am currently working to support sustainability transition for corporates at Newforesight, Netherlands.\n\nAreas of Focus: ESG, Technical Assistance, South South Collaboration, Climate Finance, Fund design, Blended Finance, Solar Energy",
